<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; PROFESSORS RECEIVE FUNDING FOR PROJECTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRED ALVAREZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two Ventura College professors have won national science grants that will 
allow them to beef up the school's math and science programs. 
</P>
<P>
 Math and science instructors Richard Quint and W. Steve Quon submitted 
proposals aimed at buying new laboratory equipment to the National Science 
Foundation.Quint was awarded $45,626, while Quon was awarded $23,159. 
</P>
<P>
 Quint's award will allow the Ventura College math department to establish a 
computer laboratory to improve students' understanding of pre-calculus and 
calculus. 
</P>
<P>
 Quon's award has been used to create a modern optics laboratory course that 
features state-of-the-art optical technologies such as lasers. 
</P>
<P>
 The national award competition is highly competitive, according to the 
National Science Foundation. Only 25% of the proposals submitted to the 
foundation's Instrumentation and Laboratory Improvement Program during the last 
fiscal year received funding. FRED ALVAREZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
