<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; LANGUAGE PROGRAM AT SCHOOL HAS 
OPENINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A few openings remain in the Capistrano Unified School District's program that 
provides bilingual and literacy education for students from homes where Spanish 
or English is predominantly spoken. 
</P>
<P>
 District officials are seeking to fill the openings with kindergarten students 
from English-speaking families. 
</P>
<P>
 The Two-Way Language Immersion Program began last year. It is being offered at 
Las Palmas Elementary School, and has drawn some students from neighboring 
school districts. 
</P>
<P>
 The program guarantees that kindergartners -- half from Spanish-speaking homes 
and half from English-speaking homes -- will be bilingual and literate in both 
languages when they move on to middle school after the fifth grade. 
</P>
<P>
 Las Palmas Elementary School, which is on a year-round calendar schedule, 
started classes Aug. 1. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call Jody Wiencek, the program's coordinator at Las 
Palmas Elementary School, at (714) 492-3456.JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
