WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; 'SILENT MOVIE NIGHT' TO OFFER CHAPLIN FILM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON GRANT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A popular Charlie Chaplin silent movie from 1914 and a live pianist will 
highlight the "Silent Movie Night Under the Stars" this evening in the Olivas 
Adobe courtyard. 
</P>
<P>
 The historical courtyard will be transformed into an outdoor movie theater for 
the event, co-sponsored by KVEN Radio and the city of Ventura Department of 
Community Services. 
</P>
<P>
 The feature film is "Tillies Punctured Romance," starring Charlie Chaplin and 
the Keystone Kops. 
</P>
<P>
 History and highlights of silent film will be discussed by Irwin Drumbrill of 
Warner Bros. studios and two comedy short films will be shown before the 
feature presentation. Pianist Janet Sendell will play along with the comedy 
shorts, giving the production a true silent movie feel. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets can be bought at Ventura City Hall. Adult tickets cost $3, children 12 
and under get in for $2 and children under 5 will be admitted free. JASON GRANT 
