<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; COUNCIL TO CONSIDER BUS FARE INCREASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bus riders in Simi Valley may be forced to pay higher fares if the City 
Council decides to hike rates to cover the increased cost of providing service. 
</P>
<P>
 The council will hold a public hearing Monday before deciding whether to 
increase regular fares from 75 cents to 90 cents and boost fares for the 
disabled from 75 cents to $1. 
</P>
<P>
 Although Simi Valley Transit is carrying more riders than ever before in its 
22-year history, fare revenue has dropped as much as 5% on some routes, while 
costs have increased nearly 6%. 
</P>
<P>
 The cost to run Simi Valley's buses at their current service level for another 
fiscal year is estimated at $1.6 million, $83,000 more than last year. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to a fare increase, the council will consider allowing advertising 
on bus shelters and cutting back on early morning and late evening service. 
</P>
<P>
 The public hearing is scheduled for 6:30 p.m. Monday at Simi Valley City Hall, 
2929 Tapo Canyon Road. SARA CATANIA 
</P>
