<TEXT>
<P>
 Sally Gunnell of Great Britain outclassed runner-up Silvia Rieger of Germany 
by more than eight meters to win the women's 400-meter hurdles final at the 
European Championships in Helsinki, Finland, the only big title missing from 
her remarkable collection. 
</P>
<P>
 Gunnell now owns Olympic, World, Commonwealth and European titles. 
</P>
<P>
 Gunnell clocked a world seasonal best of 53.33 seconds despite being 
unchallenged on the homestretch. 
</P>
<P>
 Rieger finished in 54.68 and Anna Knoroz of Russia placed third in 57.68. 
</P>
<P>
 Germany's Heike Drechsler won the long jump with an opening-round effort of 23 
feet, 5 1/4 inches. Boxing  
</P>
<P>
 Former heavyweight champion Riddick Bowe returns to the ring tonight on HBO 
against Buster Mathis Jr. in Bowe's first bout since he lost the title to 
Evander Holyfield last November. 
</P>
<P>
 Bowe, assuming a victory, has signed to fight World Boxing Council champion 
Lennox Lewis in December, or more likely, March, in a high-profile meeting of 
the two heavyweights generally considered to be more talented than champion 
Michael Moorer. Auto Racing 
</P>
<P>
 Al Unser Jr. broke the Mid-Ohio Sports Car Course track record to take the 
provisional pole for Sunday's Miller Genuine Draft 200 Indy-car race at 
Lexington, Ohio. 
</P>
<P>
 Unser, the leader in the season points standings, had a fast lap of 119.517 
m.p.h. around the 2.25-mile circuit. That bettered the mark of 118.372 m.p.h. 
set last year by Britain's Nigel Mansell. 
</P>
<P>
 Unser set his record on the last lap of qualifying. 
</P>
<P>
 Unser's Penske Racing teammates, Paul Tracy and Emerson Fittipaldi, had the 
second- and third-fastest speeds. Jurisprudence 
</P>
<P>
 A man police identified as the father of Phoenix Suns basketball player Oliver 
Miller walked into a television station, confessed to killing a Fort Worth, 
Tex. community activist, then surrendered. 
</P>
<P>
 Fort Worth television station KTVT-TV, where Oliver J. Miller turned himself 
in, identified the 54-year-old Fort Worth man as the father of the Suns 
forward. Family members told the television station the two have not spoken in 
years. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said they arrested Miller Sr. on a probable cause warrant for murdering 
Emmett Allen. 
</P>
<P>
 KTVT reported that Miller Sr. said he shot Allen on Tuesday after being 
swindled out of about $100,000 worth of properties. 
</P>
