 Re the "Boz Scaggs: Rock Takes a Snooze" review by Dennis Hunt (Aug. 8): 
</P>
<P>
 I had waited a long time to see Scaggs in concert. On Aug. 7, my wait 
ended.That voice that I have heard over the radio, on tapes, records and, yes, 
even ages ago on "The Midnight Special" has only gotten richer. The materials 
that Scaggs chose to perform, beginning with the title track of his new release 
"Some Change" to his encore pieces, "Lido" and "Dinah Flo," were great. The 
ballads that he chose to sing touched me the way that they do when I listen to 
them at home. His band and backup singers were exceptional. These were the 
songs that I had longed to hear live. I was not disappointed. 
</P>
