<HEADLINE>
<P>
NITTY-GRITTY: INSIDE & OUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times-Post News Service 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 When going on vacation, remember to stop delivery of the newspapers; have 
someone pick up your mail; set timers for lights, radios and TVs; lock all 
doors and windows and store empty trash containers. 
</P>
<P>
 * To remove mineral deposits accumulated at water level in the toilet, try 
rubbing stains with "wet" sandpaper available in hardware stores. Or, pour one 
cup of bleach into bowl; let sit for a few hours and scrub off stains. 
</P>
<P>
 * Strain fat from broth by pouring through a paper towel into container. 
</P>
<P>
 * If there isn't a water spigot near the garden or toolshed, keep a roll of 
paper towels and waterless hand cleaner or shaving cream nearby. You can clean 
your hands without water. 
</P>
</TEXT>
