<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; COLLEGE SCHEDULES LATE REGISTRATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago College will have a two-week late registration and drop/add 
period from Aug. 22 to Sept. 2 for the fall semester, a spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 During the first week of late registration, students may drop classes at the 
registration center.Students may add classes only with instructor approval and 
signature after the first week of instruction, which begins Aug. 22, spokesman 
Dale Ruhe said. 
</P>
<P>
 Drop/add forms to petition instructors will be available in the division 
offices and admissions/records offices at the Santa Ana campus, at 17th and 
Bristol streets, and the Orange campus, 8045 E. Chapman Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Information on the more than 2,000 sections of classes offered this semester 
is available in the 1994 schedule of classes, offered in campus bookstores for 
$1. Enrollment fees are $13 per unit.  
</P>
<P>
 For more information on registration and admissions procedures, call the Santa 
Ana campus at (714) 564-6000, or the Orange campus at (714) 564-4000. JON 
NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
