<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; LOS RIOS STREET ROAD WORK OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Planning Commission has approved the reconstruction of a section of 
historic Los Rios Street, but the money for the work is not yet available. 
</P>
<P>
 The commission's action this week calls for about $186,000 worth of work to 
reconstruct 1,800 feet of Los Rios Street and install new drains, according to 
city engineering officials. 
</P>
<P>
 Commissioners also approved closing a narrow L-shaped intersection between 
Mission and Los Rios streets to traffic. 
</P>
<P>
 Tom Tomlinson, the city's planning director, said the road improvements 
probably won't be made for a few years. He said the city has money to pay only 
for design work. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council, which must give final approval, is scheduled to consider the 
project Sept. 20.JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
