<HEADLINE>
<P>
TWO DRIVERS HURT IN CRASH AT INTERSECTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two drivers were critically injured Friday in a three-car collision at the 
intersection of Dale Avenue and Ball Road, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 David Louis O'Keefe, 33, of Garden Grove and Albena Phillipina Bosch, 58, of 
Stanton were reported in critical condition late Friday at UCI Medical Center 
in Orange. 
</P>
<P>
 A third driver, Viora Tira, 42, of Anaheim was treated for moderate injuries 
to her legs at West Anaheim Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses told police that shortly after 7 a.m., O'Keefe failed to stop at a 
red light at Ball Road and was struck by Tira's car, traveling south on Dale. 
The impact knocked O'Keefe's car into Bosch's. 
</P>
<P>
 No citations were issued and the investigation is continuing, police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA081394-0110 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 069494 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
August 13, 1994, Saturday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
