<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOLF TOURNAMENT TO AID VOLUNTEER CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Organizers of a benefit golf tournament in Tustin on Tuesday hope to net 
$10,000 for the Santa Ana-based Volunteer Center of Greater Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
 The tournament is scheduled for noon to 8 p.m. at Tustin Ranch Golf Course.The 
entry fee is $175 per player, which includes 18 holes of golf, lunch, a 
cocktail reception and an awards ceremony. There also will be a silent auction 
and opportunities to win vacation trips. 
</P>
<P>
 Established in 1958, the Volunteer Center is a partner of the Points of Light 
Foundation and the United Way. The center placed 27,000 volunteers at 1,200 
nonprofit agencies in Orange County last year. 
</P>
<P>
 The center also trains individuals to manage nonprofit agencies. 
</P>
<P>
 Registration for the golf tournament is available by calling Gene Anderson at 
(714) 953-5757. 
</P>
</TEXT>
