<HEADLINE>
<P>
ELDERLY WOMAN RAPED, ROBBED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A prowler broke into the home of a sleeping 76-year-old woman Friday, raped 
her and stole money she had left out, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 "The sexual assault was the motive, because it looks like the person entered 
just with that intent," said Detective Mike Coffey of the Los Angeles Police 
Department's North Hollywood Division."If anything, the taking of the property 
might have been an afterthought." 
</P>
<P>
 The woman, alone in a first-floor apartment in the 5000 block of Tujunga 
Avenue, was awakened by the rapist about 5:15 a.m., Coffey said. Her screams 
summoned the building manager and other neighbors, who helped her call 
authorities, Coffey said. 
</P>
<P>
 He added that the man probably entered through a window left open in the heat. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's something that people should be aware of and try to make themselves as 
secure as possible at night," Coffey said. 
</P>
<P>
 There have been no similar attacks in the area, police said. 
</P>
