<P>
ROLLER HOCKEY; BULLFROGS DEFEAT CALGARY IN SHOOTOUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Anaheim Bullfrogs defeated the Calgary Rad'z, 8-7, in a shootout on Friday 
at the Max Bell Centre at Calgary. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bullfrogs (13-7-1) broke a four-game losing streak and reclaimed second 
place in Roller Hockey International's Pacific Division. 
</P>
<P>
 Bob McKillop led the Bullfrogs (10-5-1) with three goals, his first hat trick 
of the season. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bullfrogs took advantage of a two-man penalty against the Rad'z and took a 
7-6 lead with less than five minutes remaining. The Rad'z (11-8-2) tied it with 
a minute to play. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bullfrogs defeated the Rad'z, 3-0, in the shootout. 
</P>
