<P>
 California SunCare Accused of Price-Fixing: The Department of Justice's 
antitrust division and the Los Angeles-based manufacturer agreed to a consent 
decree that will prohibit the company from setting a minimum resale price for 
its indoor tanning products.The Justice Department alleged that California 
SunCare set a floor price below which its distributors could not sell its 
products. But Richard Spencer, an attorney for California SunCare, denied the 
charge, saying the company agreed to the settlement -- under which the company 
does not admit wrongdoing -- to head off a lengthy and expensive court battle. 
