<TEXT>
<P>
 Micron Technology Files Petition Against South Korea: Micron's petition, filed 
with the U.S. Trade Representative, charged that South Korean semiconductor 
companies compete unfairly with U.S. chip makers, according to Electronic 
Buyers' News.Micron said in the petition that the South Korean government 
subsidizes its semiconductor companies, which gives the companies an unfair 
advantage in the U.S. market, the trade magazine said. "The combined effect of 
these programs has been to turn the Korean semiconductor industry into a 
formidable export machine," Micron said in the petition. Korean computer chip 
companies account for 28% of all dynamic random access memory chips worldwide, 
with the United States being the largest market. 
</P>
