<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEILAND, JONES HIGH ON MONEY LIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Newport Beach Dukes' Larisa Neiland and Kelly Jones finished second and 
third on the World TeamTennis' year-end prize money list. 
</P>
<P>
 Neiland, the WTT female most valuable player and female rookie of the year, 
collected $36,470.44 in helping lead the Dukes to an undefeated regular 
season.Jones, the male MVP and men's singles winner, earned $36,375. 
</P>
<P>
 Players earn a percentage of the $720,000 total prize money based on their 
season-long individual performances in singles and doubles events. The Dukes' 
Zina Garrison Jackson earned $22,798.58 and was seventh on the money list, 
while Trevor Kronemann collected $20,375 and was 10th. New Jersey's Martina 
Navratilova topped all player winnings for the fourth year in a row by earning 
$42,000. 
</P>
<P>
 Dukes Coach Angel Lopez tied New Jersey Coach Craig Kardon for first on the 
coaching money list with $9,500. 
</P>
