<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL STRIKE; DAY 1 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 At the outset of the sport's eighth work stoppage, negotiators for the players 
and owners agreed to accept federal mediation to try to resolve their 
collective bargaining stalemate.Neither side seemed optimistic of a quick fix. 
Further negotiations are unlikely until both sides meet with the mediator, who 
can only urge a settlement, not enforce one. A similar attempt was unsuccessful 
during a 50-day strike in 1981. 
</P>
<P>
 * Main story: A1 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
