<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP STAR HAS SURGERY FOR ANEURYSM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROB FERNAS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three-sport standout Phil Fonua, a defensive lineman at Mira Costa High in 
Manhattan Beach, was in critical but stable condition Friday at Torrance 
Memorial Hospital after undergoing surgery Thursday for a ruptured aneurysm in 
his brain, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The 6-foot-2, 275-pound Fonua, preparing for his senior year, collapsed 
Wednesday during a workout in the Mira Costa weight room. 
</P>
<P>
 Fonua was named Southern Section Division VII co-player of the year last 
season after helping Mira Costa win its first section football title. He also 
was starting center on the basketball team and finished fourth in the shotput 
at the State track and field meet. ROB FERNAS 
</P>
</TEXT>
